---
title: Sesame Soy Beef Bowls with Carrots, Buttery Rice & Sriracha Mayo
description: Bowls are way past “having a moment.” They’ve become a pillar of our lunches and dinners. Why? It’s simple: everything’s better in a bowl! (Nice knowing you, plates.) But seriously, the customizable combo of carbs, protein, veggies, and a drizzle of delicious sauce cannot be denied. True to form, this rendition is fully loaded. Buttery rice is topped with beef that’s glazed in a sweet and savory sesame-soy sauce, plus roasted carrots and a drizzle of creamy, spicy sriracha mayo. One bite will have you totally bowled over.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/speedy-sesame-beef-bowls-7073de59.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sesame-soy-beef-bowls-5fd0e263d3f63548ac094b5b-2439c745.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 900 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1200 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sesame-soy-beef-bowls-5fd0e263d3f63548ac094b5b
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1.5%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for
4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep
covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{4}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} with
@sriracha{2%teaspoon} to taste. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat half the @sesame oil{2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step)
in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @shredded carrots{8%ounce} and
scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a pinch of
@sugar{pinch}.

Transfer to a second small bowl and cover to keep warm.

> If there's excess grease in your pan from the beef, carefully pour it out.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for carrots over
medium high heat. Add @ground beef{20%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{8%tablespoon}, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(half the vinegar for 4 servings), and remaining sesame oil. Bring to a
simmer and cook until sauce has thickened and beef is cooked through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{2%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4
servings); season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between bowls; top with carrots and sesame soy beef. Drizzle with
sriracha mayo and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve.